 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'MikeMcC399', 'comment_id': 847204683.0, 'datetime': '2021-05-24 17:16:45+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': "I don't have an personal experience with a device which is incompatible, but I suspect that for most users of such devices that the only practical solution will be to update to a newer device. The devices which I have owned have always offered firmware updates automatically and I doubt if a device manufacturer will plan to update older firmware / device driver just because a user has contacted them.

The possibility that the only solution to the issue would be to update to a newer device is not mentioned, and I think it probably should be mentioned.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'fynngodau', 'comment_id': 847315494.0, 'datetime': '2021-05-24 20:32:27+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_2', 'text': 'I'm afraid that this is true. However, I am not in favor of adding the advice to buy a new device. It is, in most cases, not a practical solution. The (monetary and environmental) cost is at an imbalance with the benefit. For this reason, such an advice might upset users.

The should convey the advice: "Your app is working fine and your device is okay, but be aware of this limitation."

Of course depending on how this is formulated, adding the advice you proposed might make it sound more like: "It is not a good idea to use the app on this device. Better get a new one."', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'MikeMcC399', 'comment_id': 847587595.0, 'datetime': '2021-05-25 06:40:54+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': "@username_2 

- For partial incompatibility getting a new device is probably not worth it.
- For full incompatibility a new device is probably the only option if a user wants to have exposure notification capabilities linked to BLE. For environmental or cost concerns, there is also the option of obtaining a device second-hand. In any case that should be the user's decision. I just wanted to avoid raising a reader's hopes too high that they could solve the problem for their existing device.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'heinezen', 'comment_id': 847832906.0, 'datetime': '2021-05-25 12:37:32+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': "@username_1 @username_2 

IMO recommending getting a new device wouldn't come across well because it is a very expensive solution. It will sound out of touch. Of course it depends how it's worded, but I would also not be in favour of putting it in.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
