 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'tannerdolby', 'comment_id': 729238480.0, 'datetime': '2020-11-17 21:57:39+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_2', 'text': '@username_0 Does this issue still need to be handled? I'd be happy to add docs for `eleventy-cache-assets` to the main docs.

I'm not entirely sure where you want the [docs](https://github.com/11ty/eleventy-cache-assets) to be placed within the website, but I was thinking:

1. Add a permalink such as "Cache Assets" into the "Plugins" list in the "Configuration" section of the main docs. (Maybe "Cache API Requests" or "Cache Requests" would be a more suitable name)
2. Add eleventy-cache-assets [README.md](https://github.com/11ty/eleventy-cache-assets#readme) content to a template for the actual page on the site.
3. Access the eleventy-cache-assets docs page from the "Plugins" list in the main docs using `<a href="/docs/plugins/cache-assets/language/">Cache Assets</a>`. 

Below is a screenshot after I edited the html to add a list item `<li><a href="/docs/plugins/cache-assets/language/">Cache Assets</a></li>` to the "Plugins" list (prototyping before a name for the link is settled)

<img width="239" alt="Screen Shot 2020-11-17 at 1 45 17 PM" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/48612525/99454543-6a38fa80-28db-11eb-8f5a-61b9b77b219e.png">

Since the only other link to something `eleventy-cache-assets` plugin related is within [Quick Tip #009—Cache Data Requests](https://www.11ty.dev/docs/quicktips/cache-api-requests/). I thought it would be best for the `eleventy-cache-assets` docs to be within the "Plugins" unordered list as a permalink to the corresponding docs page. 

The [Read More](https://www.11ty.dev/docs/quicktips/cache-api-requests/#read-more) subheading on the quicktips page has a link to [Read more at the eleventy-cache-assets Documentation](https://github.com/11ty/eleventy-cache-assets), this link could stay the same and go to the github repo or once the docs are added with the proper menu item permalink (ie "Cache Assets") the link could go to the docs page within 11ty-website instead of linking to the external Github repository.

Let me know your thoughts! @username_0', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
